caption: I don’t think words can even explain how disrespected I felt coming to this place... I have been here before even after my fellow coworkers warned me how HORRIBLE this place is! Don’t let the name fool you, food is not fresh AT ALL, I tried the salad and it was okay not the best, but I wanted to give this place another try and I regret it so so much. I ordered the lemon grass soup and it TASTED LIKE MICROWAVED WATER WITH RAW VEGETABLES!!! That’s literally what it was, so I went back to the place NOT ASKING FOR MY MONEY BACK but to ask if they can simply remake it because I literally thought it was a mistake they made on the water soup, but very rudely the man got defensive and started treating me really horrible and told me “If you don’t like it don’t don’t buy from here” after that I respectfully told him I didn’t like the way he talked to me so I asked to speak to someone else and he told me he was the manager and he was the owner and kept saying “let’s go, let’s go” very unnecessary, so I just walked away. I don’t recommend this place at all! Very poor service and disrespectful I should’ve listen to my coworkers and not come here, there is another place down Chestnut st called Cafecito and I totally recommend that place rather than coming here trust me you will save time money and the food is way better than here. If that man is really the owner he should really learn manners and customers service.

Best option for food in water tower place for employees here in the mall on a daily basis. Healthier options, decent portions. Ask for more sauce if you like it saucy like I do. They don't have soy packets.

This place change management and this guy will nickel and dime you like no other. It’s quite disgusting. I get times are hard, but I rather you provide great service and get tipped rather be shady for extra bucks. Beware, this place makes up prices as you go, the menu price will be wrong, the company price will be inaccurate, and god forbid you use a third party app. It’s literally what this man says. So unethical. Joe and The Juice isn’t that far from here, take your business there. Or Red Mango if/when they open back up. Thank me later.
i didn't go here. I just walked by the place it looked clean though and I'm sure the staff was excellent but I will never know.
Their smoothies ar 1st rate
I had a mango tango.  And it was so good.  Yumm ymmm yumm.
Refreshing smoothies after a long walk in the city. Bill, behind the counter, made for enjoyable conversation. Would return.
Great
3 dollars for 3 bananas. Pass
Kinda pricey,  food was made by worker not wearing gloves ... quality of food was mediocre

This location has really gone downhill.  Ordered the Buddha Satay with an extra sauce on the side and cilantro.  I repeated that was extra sauce.  They had no cilantro and when I got home there was zero sauce on the noodles!  Dry and awful!  That is my last time going there.
It's ight
Really gave this place a shot, got 5 different things off the menu on different occasions, and they were each 0/10
Overpriced

Extremely disappointed in this location. I love Freshii, however this location gives small portions. I ordered the Buddha Satay and they were out of rice noodles, so I got quinoa instead. When I got my bowl it was only half full, and the veggies were mixed in with the quinoa making it look like there was more than there actually was. I’ve had Freshii several times before and the rice or grain is always on the bottom and veggies are stacked on top, right to the top of the bowl. I feel like they did this to save money on veggies. For $10.99 I expected way more than this. Now I did enjoy my meal, just wish I got the full size I ordered, I didn’t order a half size.

Put an order in online almost 2 hours before their closing time.  Called ahead to say that we were on our way since it was nearing closing time... man on the phone said they never got an order from us.  I gave him the confirmation number and said my credit card was already charged (nearly $150, I had placed an order for my entire volleyball team).  He said if I wanted to ensure they got my order, I should have come in and placed it myself.  We were at a tournament all day, that was not an option.  He refused to make any food for the kids and said they were closing soon.  He said I could contract corporate to "try to get my money back".  So ridiculous.  Anyone have an email address I could use to try to get all my money back????
Great service and food

I was very disappointed! The Bowl was just half filled, white rice instead of brown rice, lots of corn and that was it. I only saw it at the hotel and had no chance to go back and complain. That was not the Freshii I know from other locations and not worth the money.
My wife Camille bought me a very good healthy lunch from the food court at Water Tower. Delicious fish string beans and macaroni and cheese. A very healthy meal for Ira.
Just was there over the weekend! Delicious smoothies! Friendly staff! Recommended highly and will be back next time I’m in town.
Healthy food, a little expensive and bland flavor
I don't know anything about this place.
Staff was very nice and extremely patient with our big order. Food was prepared quickly and the quality was excellent.

Between all of the other Freshii places that we go to this is the best one. The food actually tastes fresh. Literally everything in the menu tastes delicious. One of our favorite things to get is their kafir (can’t remember how to spell it). The staff remember us and they are extremely friendly. We use the app to get free meals and they are fast!
Good food friendly staff, very clean.
Love it
Delicious!
Tried the kefir yogurt, loved it!
The staff is always friendly and the teriyaki twist is so good! They are welcome to LeRobs Day Spa anytime! Ask for James 😊
Try the Recoverii tumeric & fresh fruit smoothie! Yum.
Chill people and good food
I love there wraps and there can be vegetarian options as well .

Great spot to grab a quick bite.  Service is normally pretty rapid.  I would highly encourage ordering ahead via the Ritual app.  Makes picking up the food a breeze.  One downside is the restaurant itself does not have seating.  You will have to go to the foodcourt in the mall, or if the weather is nice take your food over to the Hancock plaza to eat.  Cant go wrong with any of the bowls with a smoothie.  Don't sleep on the energy bites, they are delicious.
It's alright

Great Freshii location, on a busy Friday all my friends enjoyed fantastic good roots bowls. Frozen yogurt with crainberry was a delightful desert. The cashier was fabulous fast and extremely helpful.

Do not order delivery from this place.  Found hair for a 2nd time today, on an order that was incorrect. That yellow substance between the 2 of 3 avocado slices is cheese and was just as disgusting in person, and was sitting next to a 12 inch hair. That was a double order of avo on the bowl FYI. And if you look hard enough you'll see a tiny slice of avocado that they charged 2 bucks for in the deconstructed wrap.
Great food, fun system, the workers were really nice, everyone was able to get what they wanted and we all enjoyed it.
Pretty good
Rude employees. Food was not "fresh".  The cashier was sleeping. DEFINITELY NOT GOING BACK.
Girlfriend was given wrong food.  I was given the correct order bit it was drenched in sauce and was really soggy and strong.

I ordered a buffalo Salad whereas burrito wrap was prepared .I insist on Salad however the same materials was transferred to Salad ,I thought its ok as long as it taste goods .The Salad was stale ,with no chicken pieces or 3-4 chicken pieces .Total waste of money ,trashed it . Tasteless ,couldn't have a second spoon .

Fresh fast food at decent prices. Although I do feel like before the new owners bought it, the portions were larger. Taste is still good although once I did find some old wilted spinach in my wrap and was disgusted by that. They have pretty good coffee and tea in the mornings at decent prices as well.
One of the employees was extremely rude and acted like I was inconveniencing her
Cool!

They were very disrespectful toward my partners and I when we were taking pictures for a local business to help with community outreach online with photography.  I am a BIG fan of Freshii but this location just left a bad vibe and we didn't even give them our business. They were skeptical and narrow minded about what we were trying to communicate to them in regards to a project we did for a local business in the area. I would not recommend supporting this location of Freshii and the man who runs it. If you do, you may be contributing to an establishment that does not allow innovation and compassionate communication to live.

Great place to shop for scrubs! I wish I knew about this place before today. I have never seen so many styles for male scrubs in addition to the unisex selection. I am fortunate that my dress code allows for any style/color. I have a full two week wardrobe for an incredible price and value. Higher quality uniforms. The owner is behind the counter ready to answer questions and give recommendations to help suit my needs. An overall great experience.
Water Tower place is an awesome mall to visit with all the shops available. the Mezzanine floor has a great array of food. the 7th floor has red mango for fro yo
